<br>
Actually they gained there free will when the Lich King, Ner'zhul, started losing power in Warcraft 3: The Frozen Throne. Apparently the Sword that was encased in his icy prison that he gave to Arthas to corrrupt him into the Deathknight he became in Warcraft 3: Reign of Chaos was also apart of the Lich Kings origional power. So with Frostmourne gone from withing his Frozen Throne he started losing his control on the Undead. So one undead in particular had gained enough free will to rebel against Arthas. That undead was Sylvanas Windrunner, she was an elven ranger of Quel'thalas. Arthas conquered the elven land with his legions of undead and then later raised her as a Dark Ranger as the ultimate in humiliation and servitude for standing against his army. So now she has taken her undead forces with the help of a demon and they have become the forsaken.<br>
<br>
Also, WoW doesn't portray a Diablo like setting, at least I don't think so. Any other Warcraft questions on the game, or the history just ask.<br>
